26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_timer_nv41.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:35 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "priv.h"
30#include "regsnv04.h"
31
32static void
33nv41_timer_init(struct nvkm_timer *tmr)
34{
35 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &tmr->subdev;
36 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
37 u32 f = device->crystal;
38 u32 m = 1, n, d;
39
40 /* aim for 31.25MHz, which gives us nanosecond timestamps */
41 d = 1000000 / 32;
42 n = f;
43
44 while (n < (d * 2)) {
45 n += (n / m);
46 m++;
47 }
48
49 /* reduce ratio to acceptable values */
50 while (((n % 5) == 0) && ((d % 5) == 0)) {
51 n /= 5;
52 d /= 5;
53 }
54
55 while (((n % 2) == 0) && ((d % 2) == 0)) {
56 n /= 2;
57 d /= 2;
58 }
59
60 while (n > 0xffff || d > 0xffff) {
61 n >>= 1;
62 d >>= 1;
63 }
64
65 nvkm_debug(subdev, "input frequency : %dHz\n", f);
66 nvkm_debug(subdev, "input multiplier: %d\n", m);
67 nvkm_debug(subdev, "numerator : %08x\n", n);
68 nvkm_debug(subdev, "denominator : %08x\n", d);
69 nvkm_debug(subdev, "timer frequency : %dHz\n", (f * m) * d / n);
70
71 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x009220, m - 1);
72 nvkm_wr32(device, NV04_PTIMER_NUMERATOR, n);
73 nvkm_wr32(device, NV04_PTIMER_DENOMINATOR, d);
74}
75
76static const struct nvkm_timer_func
77nv41_timer = {
78 .init = nv41_timer_init,
79 .intr = nv04_timer_intr,
80 .read = nv04_timer_read,
81 .time = nv04_timer_time,
82 .alarm_init = nv04_timer_alarm_init,
83 .alarm_fini = nv04_timer_alarm_fini,
84};
85
86int
87nv41_timer_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_timer **ptmr)
88{
89 return nvkm_timer_new_(&nv41_timer, device, index, ptmr);
90}
